82 Thus the earth was once made worthy
83 of all animal perfection;
84 thus the Virgin was made pregnant;

94 I have not spoken so that you cannot
95 clearly see that he was a king who asked for wisdom
96 so that he would be a sufficient king;

97 not to know the number in which are
98 the movers up here, or if necessary
99 ever makes necessary with contingent;

103 Therefore, if you note what I said and this,
104 that regal prudence is that seeing you learn
105 in what the arrow of my intention strikes;

109 Take my statement with this distinction;
110 and thus it can stand with what you believe
111 about the first father and our Beloved.

115 for he is rightly among the most foolish,
116 who affirms and denies without distinction
117 in one case as in the other;

124 And of this there are clear proofs in the world:
